title: Plainsmen win 2 of 3 at tourney
text:
Brandon Sun - PRINT EDITION Plainsmen win 2 of 3 at tourney 
The Crocus Plainsmen went 2-1 in its pool at a varsity girls’ volleyball tournament in Winnipeg on Friday. 
Danielle Wallace posted 19 kills as the Plainsmen beat the Sturgeon Heights Huskies 2-0 (25-18, 25-15) and Dakota Lancers 2-0 (25-16, 25-15) before falling to the Miles Macdonell Buckeyes 2-0 (25-17, 25-21). They will take on Fort Richmond in the round of 16 teams today. 
Meanwhile, the Vincent Massey Vikings went 0-3 in their pool, which features the top four teams in the provincial AAAA rankings. The Vikings lost 2-0 (25-22, 25-18) to Lord Selkirk, 2-0 (25-23, 25-14) to St. Mary’s and 2-0 (25-17, 25-11) to Massey Winnipeg. Shayla Heinrichs had 14 kills, eight digs and two blocks for the Vikings, who will play the Neelin Spartans in the round of 16. We want you to tell us what you think of our articles.
